Logic-Tools

The README is used to introduce the module and provide instructions on
how to install the module, any machine dependencies it may have (for
example C compilers and installed libraries) and any other information
that should be provided before the module is installed.

A README file is required for CPAN modules since CPAN extracts the README
file from a module distribution so that people browsing the archive
can use it to get an idea of the module's uses. It is usually a good idea
to provide version information here so that people can decide whether
fixes for the module are worth downloading.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:


	git clone https://github.com/lagutas/LogicTools.git
	cp -r LogicTools /usr/src/LogicTools
	cd /usr/src/LogicTools/Logic-Tools
	aptitude install libmodule-install-perl libconfig-inifiles-perl liblog-any-perl liblog-any-adapter-perl liblog-log4perl-perl libtest-strict-perl libtest-fixme-perl libtest-perl-critic-perl libtest-sharedfork-perl 

	wget http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/pool/main/libl/liblog-any-adapter-log4perl-perl/liblog-any-adapter-log4perl-perl_0.06-1_all.deb
	wget http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/pool/main/libt/libtest-fork-perl/libtest-fork-perl_0.02-1_all.deb


	dpkg -i liblog-any-adapter-log4perl-perl_0.06-1_all.deb
	dpkg -i libtest-fork-perl_0.02-1_all.deb

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Logic::Tools

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Logic-Tools

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Logic-Tools

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Logic-Tools

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Logic-Tools/


